        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 11:27PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1127 PM CDT/1227 AM EDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm near Stockland, or 9 miles southeast of Milford, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dunnington, Stockland, and Wellington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
